=99s larger comms apparatus that is
trying to maintain the status quo amid a historical crisis. As Dylan Byers =
explained in his excellent Curious George Stephanopoulos ( https://puck.new=
s/curious-george-stephanopoulos/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS=
+%287%2F13%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F24=
%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617d=
a42abd12a ), relations between the two entities have descended to a post-Ir=
aq War nadir. =E2=80=9CFor what it=E2=80=99s worth,=E2=80=9D Dylan wrote, =
=E2=80=9Cthe vast majority of briefing room denizens I surveyed this week t=
hink [press secretary Karine] Jean-Pierre has lost all credibility.=E2=80=
=9D In Bidenworld War ( https://puck.news/inside-biden-war-room-ahead-of-th=
e-press-conference/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F=
24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F24%29&utm_mediu=
m=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), =
Tara Palmeri reported that the
White House had even considered a seemingly desperate primetime Oval Office=
 address before settling on a slightly less illogical interview with Lester=
 Holt on Monday. (A White House spokesperson denied this.)

All of this was playing out, of course, amid the historic backdrop of NATO=
=E2=80=99s 75th anniversary, which was being commemorated in Washington las=
t week. Before Biden took the podium for his memorable press conference, Ju=
lia Ioffe gathered the chatter among the chattering classes of the internat=
ional order. NATO=E2=80=99s Five Stages of Biden Grief ( https://puck.news/=
post-biden-debate-view-from-nato-summit/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUB=
SCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2=
F13%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df=
6c60617da42abd12a ) is a sophisticated and complex piece that captures the =
funereal mood of the Western world as the Democrats attempt to handle their=
 family business
in a transcendentally messy fashion. Puck, as I=E2=80=99ve noted before, en=
deavors to be the biography of our age, one day at a time. Amid the heat an=
d unpredictability of this ground-shifting July, I couldn=E2=80=99t be more=
 proud of my partners=E2=80=99 reporting, which captures the nuances and st=
akes of the moment.

But if you=E2=80=99re currently in need of a break from the Biden crisis, p=
erhaps searching for something a little beachier, I=E2=80=99d turn your att=
ention to Rachel Strugatz=E2=80=99s excellent and illuminating piece ( http=
s://puck.news/you-can-get-a-goop-facial-at-new-goop-store/?utm_campaign=3DT=
he+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+=
SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F13%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustom=
er.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) on Gwyneth Paltrow=E2=80=99s latest p=
ivot at Goop. It=E2=80=99s hard to recall, but Paltrow was the culture=E2=
=80=99s first A-list movie star to fully cross over into the world of lifes=
tyle entrepreneurship=E2=80=94a
prescient decision that shaped the mid-careers of innumerable followers. Go=
op, her woo-woo and beauty company, was initially derided for all the obvio=
us reasons. More than a decade later, Paltrow remains C.E.O., and she=E2=80=
=99s embarking on an executive and strategic shake-up. The dynamics of the =
shift=E2=80=94both the strategy, itself, and the hybrid identity of its arc=
hitect=E2=80=94are representative of these strange times we=E2=80=99re livi=
ng through. Indeed, it=E2=80=99s merely one of the great plotlines of our a=
ge, and precisely what you should expect to read in Puck.

Have a great weekend,
Jon

