YxMyUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTK=
yUyODclMkYxMyUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1f=
c291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW5=
0ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjo5NTA0NTd9/15b04798c06f6=
2c42e06ad6bf7e1c45c9bfe32f4e924fecb23667205c2c26cbc" style=3D"color:#d40000=
;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">Biden vs. The World</=
a></u></i>, the president=E2=80=99s normally unified and lockstep inner cir=
cle has, to steal one of the piece=E2=80=99s most choice lines, turned into=
 a circular firing squad that makes the final scene of <i>Reservoir Dogs </=
i>look like a Merchant Ivory period piece. Naturally, this explains all the=
 pernicious and obfuscatory leaking that fingered former chief of staff <b>=
Ron Klain </b>for overpreparing Biden at Camp David and top advisor <b>Anit=
a Dunn </b>for advising a communications strategy that kept the president i=
n bubble wrap. <br/><br/>And then there=E2=80=99s the battle taking shape b=
etween the journalists who cover the White House, many of whom feel duped, =
and the president=E2=80=99s larger comms apparatus that is
trying to maintain the status quo amid a historical crisis. As <b>Dylan Bye=
rs </b>explained in his excellent <i><u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/=
e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dRckNBbmt6aEQ3aWFRM2hyaTB3ND0=
