NjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6OTUzMDEwfQ/09432763a61c0a8c784813929db2=
067b74c36049e8de7f563bbec8527d9d5cb0" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoratio=
n:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">illuminating piece</a></u> on <b>Gwy=
neth Paltrow</b>=E2=80=99s latest pivot at Goop. It=E2=80=99s hard to recal=
l, but Paltrow was the culture=E2=80=99s first A-list movie star to fully c=
ross over into the world of lifestyle entrepreneurship=E2=80=94a
prescient decision that shaped the mid-careers of innumerable followers. Go=
op, her woo-woo and beauty company, was initially derided for all the obvio=
us reasons. More than a decade later, Paltrow remains C.E.O., and she=E2=80=
=99s embarking on an executive and strategic shake-up. The dynamics of the =
shift=E2=80=94both the strategy, itself, and the hybrid identity of its arc=
hitect=E2=80=94are representative of these strange times we=E2=80=99re livi=
ng through. Indeed, it=E2=80=99s merely one of the great plotlines of our a=
ge, and precisely what you should expect to read in Puck.<br/><br/>Have a g=
reat weekend,<br/>Jon<br/></td>
